.TH "rvt_map_mr_sg" 9 "rvt_map_mr_sg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rvt_map_mr_sg \- map sg list and set it the memory region
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rvt_map_mr_sg
.BI "(struct ib_mr *ibmr "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "int sg_nents "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *sg_offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ibmr" 12
memory region
.IP "sg" 12
dma mapped scatterlist
.IP "sg_nents" 12
number of entries in sg
.IP "sg_offset" 12
offset in bytes into sg
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Overwrite rvt_mr length with mr length calculated by ib_sg_to_pages.
.SH "RETURN"
number of sg elements mapped to the memory region
